
## ðŸ§© Types of Class Members

| Type                 | Description                                                                           |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Member Variables** | Also called **attributes** or **fields** â€” they store data about the object.          |
| **Member Functions** | Also called **methods** â€” they define the behavior or actions the object can perform. |

---

## âœ… Example

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class Person {
public:
    // ðŸ”¹ Member Variables
    string name;
    int age;

    // ðŸ”¹ Member Function
    void introduce() {
        cout << "Hi, I'm " << name << " and I'm " << age << " years old." << endl;
    }
};
```

---

## ðŸ§ª Using Class Members

```cpp
int main() {
    Person p1;         // Create an object
    p1.name = "Sofiane";
    p1.age = 21;

    p1.introduce();    // Call member function
    return 0;
}
```

---

## ðŸ” Access Specifiers (control access to members)

| Specifier   | Meaning                                                        |
| ----------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `public`    | Members are accessible from outside the class.                 |
| `private`   | Members are **only accessible inside the class**.              |
| `protected` | Like `private`, but accessible in child classes (inheritance). |

### Example with `private`:

```cpp
class Account {
private:
    double balance;

public:
    void deposit(double amount) {
        balance += amount;
    }

    double getBalance() {
        return balance;
    }
};
```

---

## ðŸ§  Summary

| Member Type       | Example             | Description                   |
| ----------------- | ------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| Variable (field)  | `string name;`      | Stores object's data          |
| Function (method) | `void introduce();` | Performs an action            |
| Object uses them  | `p1.name = "Ali";`  | Access/modify them via object |

